DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$b1 = random(6,10,1);
$coef3 = 2;
$coef2 = 3*($a1+$b1);
$coef1 = 6*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = random(1,11,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = -$coef3 x^3 + $coef2 x^2 - $coef1 x + $coef0 \).
For this function there are three important intervals:
 \( (-\infty, A] \), \( [A,B] \), and \( [B,\infty) \) where
 \( A \) and  \( B \) are the critical numbers.
$BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $a1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is increasing (type in INC) or decreasing (type in DEC).
$BR
 \( (-\infty, A] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [A,B] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "INC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [B,\infty) \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
 \( f(x) \) has an inflection point at \( x =C \)
 $BR
where \( C \) is \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = ($a1+$b1)/2;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
Finally for each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is concave up (type in CU) or concave down (type in CD).
$BR
 \( (-\infty, C] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "CU";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [C,\infty) \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "CD";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
